Skarphed on Mac OS X:

Steps taken to get it run (tested on Mac OS 10.8 Mountain Lion)
INFO: do the steps b to e in Terminal.app

a) Install these programms
   - XQuarz (
   - pip
   - port
   - brew (install this under a second user it could convict with port)

b) Install python libs
   - sudo pip install pycrypto
   - sudo pip install paramiko
   - sudo pip install fdb
   - sudo pip install tinycss

c) Install GTK (login to the user where you've installed brew)
   NOTE: I had to do this twice the first time just GTK+ came without pygtk
   - brew install pygtk
   - brew install pygtk

d) Export $PYTHONPATH and make it permanent -> pythonÂ´s lib locations
   - echo "export PYTHONPATH=/usr/local/lib/python2.7/site-packages:/usr/local/lib/python2.7/site-packages:$PYTHONPATH" >> ~.profile
   - echo "export PYTHONPATH=/Library/Python/2.7/site-packages/:$PYTHONPATH" >> ~.profile

e) To run Skarphed
   - cd ../admin/src/
   - python Application.py

   Gratulations you're done. Skarphed is now running on your Macintosh!

